  "prompt": "My username is no longer available on Skype. Why?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why your Skype username is no longer available:\n\n1. **Account Deletion**: If you or someone else deleted your account, the username may no longer exist.\n\n2. **Inactivity**: Skype may recycle usernames from inactive accounts. If your account has been inactive for a long period, it might have been deactivated.\n\n3. **Policy Changes**: Skype might have updated their policies regarding usernames, causing some usernames to be retired or suspended.\n\n4. **Suspension/Ban**: If your account was found to be in violation of Skype's terms of service, your username could be suspended or banned.\n\n5. **Username Changes**: If Skype has undergone updates or changes in their username format (e.g., transitioning to Microsoft accounts), your old username may have been affected.\n\nIf you're unsure about the status of your account or username, you may want to contact Skype support for assistance.",
